{"lemma":"فَلاحٌ","slug":"فَلاحٌ","root":"ف.ل.ح","root_slug":"ف-ل-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ل-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34484","n34488"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AD%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a farmer, a peasant","tags":["countable"],"examples":[{"text":"هٰؤُلَاءِ الْفَلَّاحُونَ مِنْ تِلْكَ الْقَرْيَةِ الْمِصْرِيَّةِ الْكَبِيرَةِ.","english":"These farmers are from that big Egyptian village."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"success","tags":["uncountable"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ف ل ح (f l ḥ). The sense of \"farmer\" is assumed to be borrowed from Aramaic פלחא / ܦܠܚܐ (pallāḥā, “worker; peasant”), owing to the dominant economy of Arabic speakers being nomadic when in contrast Aramaic speakers practised agriculture. This assumed, فَلَحَ (falaḥa, “to furrow, to plow; to slit, to cleave”) would be denominal."},"ipa":["/fal.laːħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34484","headword_ar":"فَلَاحٌ","root":"flH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, L, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaHN","text_ar":"فَلَحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) the latter a contraction of the former, (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Prosperity; success;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attainment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquisition, of that which one desires"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, L, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of that whereby one becomes in a happy and good state."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Safety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"security."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Continuance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"permanence, in a good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosperous, state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the enjoyment of ease, comfort,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the blessings of life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuance of good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuance, permanence, lastingness, duration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endurance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISK, S, L.) There is not in the language of the Arabs any word more comprehensive in its significations of what is good in the present life and in the final state than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfalaAHu","text_ar":"الفَلَاحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a","text_ar":"حَىَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlfalaAHo","text_ar":"عَلَى الفَلَاحْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the call to prayer, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come ye to the means of the attainment of Paradise, and of permanence therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hasten to the attainment of everlasting life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come to safety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"security:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come ye to the way of safety and prosperity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come to the continuance of good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^afoEalu *`lika falaAHa Ald~ahori","text_ar":"لَا اَفْعَلُ ذٰلِكَ فَلَاحَ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do that while time lasts."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wal`kino layosa lild~unoyaA falaAHu"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"But there is not to the present state of existence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lastingness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endurance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) ―         -b2-  Also (both words) (tropical:)  The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHuwr","text_ar":"سَحُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is eaten a little before daybreak previously to commencing a day's fast"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, A, L, K:) so called because thereby is the continuing of the fast; (S, A;) or because of the lastingness of its utility. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","A","Mgh","Msb","IAth"]},{"entry_id":"n34488","headword_ar":"فَلَّاحٌ","root":"flH","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A plougher, tiller,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cultivator, of land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a peasant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, Msb, K, TA;) because he cleaves ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafolaHu","text_ar":"يَفْلَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$uq~u","text_ar":"يَشُقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":") the land: (TA:) [pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fal~aAHuwna","text_ar":"فَلَّاحُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] coll. gen. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fal~aAHapN","text_ar":"فَلَّاحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) ―         -b2-  And [hence, as being likened to a plougher,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A seaman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sailor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a servant of ships"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boats."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who lets asses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other beasts, on hire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mukaArK","text_ar":"مُكَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, K, TA:) so called as being likened to the plougher, &c., of land. (TA.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who defrauds in a sale, in the manner described in the explanation of the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaHa bihi","text_ar":"فَلَحَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","T","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}